I was going to get this place 3 stars because it didn't give me food poisoning, was pizza, and was reasonably tasty, but it turns out that I spent $80 on two pizzas and a chicken. Apparently, they recently updated their menu and increased their prices significantly and didn't bother to tell me when I ordered. < review>
This is by far the most professional and friendly locksmith business I have every patronized! HIGHLY RECOMMEND!
When I had initially called in to see if they were able to cut an automotive key for my honda, Ruben was incredibly polite and patient on the phone and in person. Being a sceptical after several calls to other businesses, I am sure I sounded exhausted and defeated. I had called three other places explaining my situation and all other competitors audibly laughed and said no.
When I arrived at their brick and mortar, I was pleasantly surprised to see a professional and well stocked interior and was greeted immediately!
I mentioned that I had just called about my honda key, and Ruben immediately took the initiative to offer relocating the rfid transponder the the new casing at no additional charge. Talk about going above and beyond! When I had mentioned that the battery may also be depleted in the remote, he voiced that he absolutely had the replacement in stock! The frugal natured person that I am was shocked when the replacement battery was priced exactly what I'd pay on amazon for it, and they even replaced the old one.
All in all, I was amazed at the quality of service I received, and will be returning for all of my replacement key needs!
Thank you Team!<//review>

<user_id>107004005991219349364< /user_id><username>Diana C< /username>< date>
1622868909840<//date>
<Rate>5< /Rate>< Text>
We were doing a remodel/addition to our home and needed all new base molding: 280 linear feet.  I spent one hour at HD looking at all the options and pricing and left frustrated.

Hubby said to go to Builders Molding Supply before I came home because our uncle had recommended them for doors.

I walked inside and instantly was welcomed, was asked all the pertinent questions about my project and shown some initial options.  I showed him a picture of the door casings and gave him an idea of the look we wanted.  He suggested a 3.5" molding and gave me a price that made my eyes bug out in a good way!  It was $2 less than the molding I was considering at HD!  I asked if he had enough in stock (eighteen pieces of 16' lengths) and he assured he did.  I paid for it and sent hubby to pick up within 30 minutes.

The whole process from when I walked in to when I walked out took maybe 15 minutes.  All the guys were friendly and professional.  I noticed they had doors, drawer pulls and other details for the home.  I won't ever try HD or the competition first ever again!<//Text>

< review>
Hawthorne Motors Express was an absolute pleasure to deal with. They made the process quick and easy. They are very flexible and will never try to pressure sell you. As a commercial real estate broker, I am not a fan of using emotion to sell and not once did they try to do that. I was looking at another car at South Bay Land Rover, which was a used Volvo S40. Not only were they unwilling to negotiate (the vehicle was priced about $700 above what they should have charged based on comparable vehicles I found at other dealers), but they attempted to constantly pressure me into signing paperwork, filling out a credit application, etc. They were also bombarding me with calls and emails. Other dealers (as well as South Bay Land Rover) also tried to sway me by asking me "to get in the car one more time" or "test drive it another time." Sorry, folks, but those tactics do not work on me.

I would also like to especially give recognition to Tarren and Sara for being very flexible with me. It took me over two weeks to finally decide on my 2008 MINI Cooper S Convertible after a couple of inspections and some negotiating.

I would highly recommend this dealership. This is by far the best experience I have had in buying a car.< /review>

< Text>
The team at Hawthorne Motors Express was wonderful. I can't recommend them highly enough. They are friendly, honest, helpful, proactive, and knowledgeable. This was about the best car-buying experience I could imagine, and they demonstrated the best of what I hope for and expect in an auto dealership.

I was in the market for a pre-owned SUV and had done about 20 hours of research before deciding on three possible models and a range of model years. They had exactly what I was looking for in terms of budget, mileage, vintage, maintenance records, and condition.

Terran was very friendly when I arrived, and took as much time as I needed to take a test drive, look over the car, answer my questions, and get me all the information I needed to help me decide. There was no pressure, and I felt that he genuinely wanted me to find the best car for my needs. Building a customer relationship was primary; making an immediate sale wasn't the priority.

Sara was proactive and positive while working with me on arranging the best financing terms. Hawthorne has excellent relationships with many lenders and she spent as much time as it took to get me very fair terms.

The purchase process was smooth, no pressure, transparent, and easy. But what really exceeded my expectations was how they handled an issue with the car that showed up about a week after I bought it. The car I bought was a few years old and had higher miles (over 100,000), and so was sold as-is without a warranty.

When I started experiencing transmission issues after purchase, I was disappointed but not surprised (all model year Chevy Traverses are known to have transmission issues, and I knew this going in). When I reached out to Sara, she told me to come by anytime that was convenient for me.

The issue was not with the transmission, but with the torque converter, and after exhaustive research both online and talking to knowledgeable friends, I was confident there was no way they could have known about this issue before it showed up. Despite having sold me the car as-is (no warranty), Sara enthusiastically worked with me to find a transmission specialist to correctly diagnose the problem and help me decide on a course of action to repair the issue, given that the issue was complicated and many things couldn't be known before the transmission was opened up and inspected (the car wasn't throwing any error codes). It helped that Hawthorn has been around a long time and has built a solid reputation and network with auto specialists around Southern CA, which they bring to the table to help their clients in situations just like this.

When the repair estimate came in, Sara negotiated a better deal on my behalf and kicked in a few hundred dollars to defray the costs. I am 100% satisfied with how Hawthorne handled my purchase and the transmission problem that showed up. They weren't obligated to do what they did based on the purchase contract, but it shows that they care about doing right by their customers and building lasting relationships that they did what they did.

Hawthorne has impeccable business practices and showed me exactly what a used auto dealership should be.<//Text>

<rating>5< /rating>< review>
Not your average used car dealership. They buy better cars and most importantly, they actually go through the cars and make repairs--even major ones if necessary. We were fortunate to find the car we were looking for for our daughter, BMW X3, at this dealership. It was by far the best one we saw (we saw 16 of them in 2 months of looking) and the price was on the money. To be honest, their prices on everything we saw there were extremely fair--priced to move. Since they know this, they don't like to deal much; not much need really as they are extremely fair. With our X3, they put on brand new Pirelli tires, new brakes and rotors and had a window regulator repaired with OEM parts. We asked for two keys and they even did that for us. The owners are family and in the end made us feel as though they really cared that our daughter's first car was going to be safe, reliable and as close to new as possible. Quite a breath of fresh air when it comes to used car dealerships. You can be confident in a purchase from this place...for sure!< /review>

< Review>
My wife and I were shopping for a commuter, hybrid car and through our online search found what seemed to be a great deal, the best actually. We were very reluctant at first because we have never purchased a car from a small dealer. Needless to say we were skeptical.
We arrived at the lot and instantly felt welcomed and valued. The staff wasn't pushy, but very accommodating. The car was just as described except for a broken fog light. Still, my wife and I contemplated not buying it because it seemed too good be true and we suspected maybe the car had a bad history. After a test drive, close inspection, carfax review and a promise to order and install the fog light we decided to take a chance.
Turned out to be be one of the best purchases we ever made and the best car buying experience we've ever had, and we've bought lots of cars.
Sara made the financing process a real pleasure and Hoss was the nicest most sincere man we've come across in a long while. He bought my wife and I lunch and continuously ensured we were comfortable.
It's been a few weeks and we couldn't be happier, Hoss came through with his promise to order and install the broken fog light and we haven't come across another deal this good yet.
I highly recommend Hawthorne Motors Express and look forward to the opportunity to refer business there way.
Thanks to all the staff.
FYI: I've never written a review before. But this was a worthy experience and the way business should be conducted.<//Review>

She was really gracious as well; throughout the process, everyone was very nice, respectful, and accommodating. Hoss is very fair and a quite reasonable negotiator. My mechanic did find something needed repair; the right strut was leaking.  We came to an agreement through which he arranged for it to be repaired and covered the cost in lieu of repainting an area of the car with minor scratches, which was fair. Great family, great experience!< /Review>

<Rating>4</Rating>< Review>
One of the best car buying experience of our lives...Stumbled upon Hawthorne Motors Express, in Lawndale, via the internet. We were looking for a specific car and this dealership was advertising this car, but the site didn't include any pictures, they had recently just acquired the car. I called for more than a week, everyday, inquiring about internet pictures and was told for more than a week that, they were detailing the car, and pictures would be put up that day or they would email me the pics; the pictures were never put up online, or emailed; So, my family and I finally drove down from Murrieta to Lawndale to check out the car. This is the only reason why I didn't grade them excellent.

Upon immediately seeing the dealership I was a little skeptical, because it's a small mom and pop dealership, but they had a great selection of cars no older than 2006 and the prices were impressive. We were immediately greeted by the owners daughter, Sara, and the owner himself Hoos, came over later to introduce himself. They were very friendly and immediately directed us to the car we were interested in. They gave us time to inspect the car w/o pressure, the imperfections we addressed and immediately taken care of, the test drive was great, and when we asked to take the vehicle to an independent shop of our choice to get it inspected, there were no objections. At no time did we feel pressured into purchasing this car.

We decided to purchase the car, after getting it checked out, and while the car was priced below 'Kelly Blue Book' value, we negotiated and got Hoos to reduce the purchase price even more. From the time we began the paper, til the end, it took maybe 15 minutes. My husband and I have purchased more than 10 cars in our lifetime and we've never had such a wonderful experience. This is a dealership that I would definitely recommend to family and friends.

RJ Rice<//Review>

<date>1434661736906<//date>< review>
My engine light went on a few days ago, not knowing it would cause for my smog check to fail, I brought it in for its smog check.  When I got to Barstow Smog Check, the tech told me there would be a fee whether it passed or failed.  He then asked me if my engine light was on, when I told him it had gone on a few days back, he recommended that I get it checked by my mechanic first because that would automatically fail the smog.  I followed his advise, took my car in to a mechanic, thankfully it was a minor fix (gas cap).  When I brought my car back for its smog, it passed!  I am so glad and thankful that the tech was honest with me on my first visit. He saved me $53.  I would definitely recommend this place.< /review>

Service and food were good. The waitstaff was accommodating, and was often enough at-elbow to refresh glasses but not so much so that you felt bothered by their presence. As far as dining experience goes, I would recommend it for someone looking to spend some time sitting down to eat but not spend a large amount of money; however, if you are looking to dine on a budget, I would suggest you look elsewhere, since the prices tend to the low side of mid-range. <Rate>5</Rate><Text>My first visit definitely made a positive impact. Great location within the always awesome River Park complex. I live in another town, but visit Fresno for a variety of reasons. And a hot lunch with a cold beer happens to be one of them.

And with maybe 120 options for a cold brew, who could ask for anything more! Brews are a world of their own, and the helpful barman sure knew his business. Samples available upon request.

I commented on the hefty menu, 3 pages of beers!, then reviewed a great selection of appetizers, salads, light lunches (halfsies), and full-on dinners. Whew!

I mentioned it was my first visit and was informed there are maybe 80 locations nationwide. Call me clueless. Another buddy in Bako says theirs isn't open yet.

When you're in North Fresno and are hungry and thirsty, check out the Yard House.</Text>< pictures>

<rating>5< /rating>< text>
So. Many. Choices.

Looking for a restaurant that can accomodate our family, which includes one vegan, can be challenging.  Yard House really came through for us.  Lots of great beers on tap.  Many vegan and vegetarian options.  A menu that goes on for days.

Everything was delicious.

We did have a hiccup where there was a long delay on a couple of items, due to a staff mistake.  However, the server and the manager proactively let us know about the delay before we even noticed, and offered to tide us over with a salad or appetizer while we waited.  They adjusted the bill appropriately without our having to ask.  Take note, business owners.  Mistakes happen.  They needn't be a detriment.  They can be an opportunity to shine.<//text>

<review>I had lunch at Yard House recently. I ordered from the Oktoberfest (German inspired dishes) menu. I had the Bavarian Pork Chops, two lightly encrusted chops with wild mushroom sauce, baby broccoli and parmesan mashed potatoes. The chops were quite juicy and flavorful. The mushroom gravy was tasty and savory. The broccoli was perfectly cooked on the grill, and the potatoes tasted very good. I couldn't distinguish the parmesan, which was a bonus, since I actually don't care for the its taste. All in all a very good meal.< /review>< Pictures>

< Name>
Narcissyphus Phenomenonsense<//Name>
< time>
1574182779281</time>
< Review>
My family and I went to Yard House for a last family gathering before I left for my first duty station in the UK. Being that my sister and aunt are vegans, and knowing that Yard House has some excellent vegan options for food and beer, we all settled in with going to Yard House. We were quickly greeted at the door. It was a very busy night inside so we chose to sit on  the patio. The heater had gone out and we were told that they were unwilling to exchange the heating lamp with another empty tables heating lamp. We then ordered the Gardein Pepper Whiskey Wings, and a few other vegan options for our entrees.

Our waiter was nice enough, but only took one order of beer I stead of the entirety of the table. We got our food pretty quickly but had to search for our waiter to get our beers ordered. It was busy after all. We received all of our food at once, appetizer included.

I, not being vegan but having a culinary background and having had the Gardein here before, was immediately befuddled when I realized the appetizer wasn't Gardein. My family and I all decided to make a game of it and try to figure it out. It wasn't until I tried my sister's Gardein Orange Chicken when I finally told them, "You need to stop eating the wings." I explained myself and the food. Our waiter assured us it was Gardein. When we received the bill... SURE ENOUGH. They were not. We were charged for an original order of Whiskey Pepper Wings... We told the waiter and he never took it off the bill. I believe my vegan family members were lead believing that they were eating a vegan appetizer and then decided to charge them for an improperly order item. I'm not saying this is a bad place. I'm not even mad about it. But, I just thought I would share that for everyone.<//Review>

<Review>My friends wanted to celebrate my birthday and told me to choose a place to eat. I've never had a problem with Yard House ever. It's been a favorite for me until 4/23/18. I was craving steak and got the 12oz ribeye for $30. I asked for medium well and my steak over extremely well-done and over charred. All I could taste was how burnt the steak was. I'm not a big complainer in general, and so my friend told our server, named Ross, that I was unsatisfied with my meal. I did basically eat my whole plate because my friends and I were waiting for my other friends over an hour so we were starving and therefore, I ate what I had. Ross was nice enough to take my meal to let I believe he's the kitchen manager, or some type of manager in the back know. The manager, Angel came out and told me if I were dissatisfied with my meal, I should have said something from the beginning instead of saying nothing. I told him I'm not much of a complainer therefore was too shy to speak up, and he said it's not about complaining but making the food right for you. If that was the case, he should have noticed that my steak was not medium well from the first place. Angel just had a nasty attitude and ruined my ruined meal. However, Ross is such a great server. He apologized on behalf of Angel and said he handled the situation in the wrong manner. So I'm thankful for Ross. But this problem will definitely make me not come back to Yard House for awhile/ever get steak from here.< /Review>< Pictures>

< Review>
Wait staff is great.  Drinks and food came in a timely manner and we were checked on regularly.

All the appetizers during happy hour were very good but I won't order the Ahi Sashimi again.  It didn't taste bad but fancy foo-foo sushi dishes isn't our thing.  Sliced fish, ginger, wasabi, maybe julienne radish....but that's all that's needed for sashimi.  There was a sauce on the plate that everything sat on.

The bill was lower than expected during happy hour deals.  Would come again when in the area.< /Review>

<Time>1421177161142<//Time><rate>1<//rate>< Review>
Horrible customer service with mediocre food.  I ordered a mixed drink and could hardly taste the alcohol, had to send it back to be made properly.  Ordered the mushroom lettuce wrap as an appetizer, the server did not mention that the plate and food on the plate were boiling lava hot.  After picking up a lettuce wrap I realized how hot it was and dropped it immediately.  I now have 2nd degree burns across my hand.  The server handled the situation very poorly.  She was arguing that the food was hot at the bottom.  Regardless, finger foods should never ever be served to a customer hot enough to burn the skin.  This place has potential but lacking attention to detail.  I recommend this place go through a change of management and better training for the servers and bus boys.</Review>
